<div class="fusion-text"><h1><span style="color: #ffffff;">Fascination</span></h1>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">Diamonds fascinate, are favorite pieces, status symbols and value investment at the same time. The myth diamond lives. Why is that really so?</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">Diamonds are the oldest gems of our creation. Many were born in the fiery depths of the earth 3 billion years ago and most of them are already more than 100 million years old. Their sparkling power and their mysterious sparkle have always enchanted people. The ancient Greeks considered them splinters from fallen stars. Modern romantics see in their timeless beauty the symbol of pure immortality. Diamonds can only be cut by diamonds. Diamonds do not erode and scratch like other stones, so the statement is correct, diamonds are forever.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">In order to be able to determine its value in principle, there are four criteria: the 4 Cs: Carat, Cut, Color and Clarity. In German: weight, cut, color and purity.</span></p>
